1
00:00:00,979 --> 00:00:05,810
If I show you this chart, can you tell which
time frame I’m using?

2
00:00:05,810 --> 00:00:06,810
NO!

3
00:00:06,810 --> 00:00:11,340
If you view a chart on a one minute, hourly
or daily timeframe, you wouldn’t be able

4
00:00:11,340 --> 00:00:13,950
to distinguish one from the other.

5
00:00:13,950 --> 00:00:18,539
That is because the price action on the charts
have fractal characteristics.

6
00:00:18,539 --> 00:00:22,660
We can see similar patterns at various time
frequencies.

7
00:00:22,660 --> 00:00:26,589
This is a very important topic in trading
and today you’ll learn how to correctly

8
00:00:26,589 --> 00:00:28,820
trade market fractals.

9
00:00:28,820 --> 00:00:36,670
So if you could, like, subscribe to the channel
and stick around for the full video.

10
00:00:36,670 --> 00:00:39,910
What are Fractals?

11
00:00:39,910 --> 00:00:45,489
At the very core, a market fractal is the
basic building block of price movements up

12
00:00:45,489 --> 00:00:46,989
and down.

13
00:00:46,989 --> 00:00:50,700
Fractals indicate market turning points or
swing points.

14
00:00:50,700 --> 00:00:55,770
Every support or resistance formed in your
charts first start with a fractal.

15
00:00:55,770 --> 00:01:01,000
You can see why fractals are one of the best
tools especially when trading price action.

16
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:05,800
In any trading decision, it is critical to
find support and resistance areas, whatever

17
00:01:05,800 --> 00:01:09,320
timeframe we are looking at.

18
00:01:09,320 --> 00:01:14,550
Fractals were introduced by Bill Williams
in his book "Trading Chaos".

19
00:01:14,550 --> 00:01:19,490
Fractals are centered on the idea that there
is repetition in price behavior and they can

20
00:01:19,490 --> 00:01:22,870
provide an insight into the repetition patterns.

21
00:01:22,870 --> 00:01:28,360
The indicator usually looks like a five bars
model which is aimed to identify possible

22
00:01:28,360 --> 00:01:32,420
reversal points and detect the direction of
the price.

23
00:01:32,420 --> 00:01:37,850
In order to detect a fractal formation you
must look at five successive price bars where

24
00:01:37,850 --> 00:01:43,000
the third (or the middle) bar represents the
highest high or the lowest low.

25
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:48,650
In an up fractal the middle bar will have
a higher high than both of the bars at either

26
00:01:48,650 --> 00:01:50,200
side of it.

27
00:01:50,200 --> 00:01:55,460
In a down fractal the middle bar will have
a lower low than both of the bars at either

28
00:01:55,460 --> 00:01:56,700
side of it.

29
00:01:56,700 --> 00:02:02,290
Keep in mind that the fractal arrow appears
only above or below the third candlestick

30
00:02:02,290 --> 00:02:07,230
if it is the highest or the lowest of the
five bars.

31
00:02:07,230 --> 00:02:12,760
A bearish fractal pattern, which indicates
a market reversal to the downside, forms when

32
00:02:12,760 --> 00:02:18,230
each of three successive candlesticks shows
price recoding a higher high, followed by

33
00:02:18,230 --> 00:02:23,920
two candlesticks showing price action with
a lower high than the high of the preceding

34
00:02:23,920 --> 00:02:24,920
candlestick.

35
00:02:24,920 --> 00:02:28,400
Bearish fractal pattern serves as resistance.

36
00:02:28,400 --> 00:02:33,620
A bullish fractal pattern, which indicates
a market reversal to the upside, forms when

37
00:02:33,620 --> 00:02:38,890
each of three successive candlesticks show
price moving to a lower low, followed by two

38
00:02:38,890 --> 00:02:44,959
candlesticks showing price action with a higher
low than the low of the preceding candlestick.

39
00:02:44,959 --> 00:02:48,870
This fractal acts as a support level.

40
00:02:48,870 --> 00:02:53,810
Fractals provide more reliable signals on
higher time frames, but it will also display

41
00:02:53,810 --> 00:02:55,420
fewer signals.

42
00:02:55,420 --> 00:03:00,790
Obviously, depending on what time frame you’re
using, the absolute amount of time required

43
00:03:00,790 --> 00:03:03,370
to form a fractal pattern varies.

44
00:03:03,370 --> 00:03:08,659
If you’re using the hourly chart, a fractal
pattern can form in five hours.

45
00:03:08,659 --> 00:03:13,230
If you trade the daily chart, you will see
fractal patterns that form over the course

46
00:03:13,230 --> 00:03:14,600
of five days.

47
00:03:14,600 --> 00:03:19,920
One of the advantages of fractal pattern is
that it is relatively easy to spot on a chart.

48
00:03:19,920 --> 00:03:25,209
Notice here how the middle bar within the
up fractal has the highest high of the entire

49
00:03:25,209 --> 00:03:31,189
five bar structure, and how each of the two
bars preceding it and following it have a

50
00:03:31,189 --> 00:03:32,689
lower high.

51
00:03:32,689 --> 00:03:37,230
This creates a level of resistance in the
market, and the expectation is for price to

52
00:03:37,230 --> 00:03:42,049
continue lower until the next down fractal
forms in the market.

53
00:03:42,049 --> 00:03:46,760
When you look at the middle bar within a down
fractal, you can see that it has the lowest

54
00:03:46,760 --> 00:03:52,930
low of the entire five bar structure, and
that each of the two bars immediately before

55
00:03:52,930 --> 00:03:55,500
and after it have a higher low.

56
00:03:55,500 --> 00:04:00,279
This creates a level of support in the market
and an expectation for price to move higher

57
00:04:00,279 --> 00:04:04,930
until the next up fractal forms in the price
action.

58
00:04:04,930 --> 00:04:09,040
The structure of the market fractals is fairly
simple to understand.

59
00:04:09,040 --> 00:04:13,940
You can build many different trading rules
and models around the concept of fractals.

60
00:04:13,940 --> 00:04:15,519
But, very important.

61
00:04:15,519 --> 00:04:21,390
The fifth candle in a fractal pattern must
close before you make trading decisions.

62
00:04:21,390 --> 00:04:26,190
This is because the price can move during
the time the fifth candle is forming.

63
00:04:26,190 --> 00:04:32,000
If price moves either above the higher high
or below the lower low, while the pattern

64
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:37,410
is still forming, the fractal indicator will
disappear from your price chart.

65
00:04:37,410 --> 00:04:42,260
So you must wait for the pattern to complete
in order to make sure that the fractal is

66
00:04:42,260 --> 00:04:43,260
confirmed.

67
00:04:43,260 --> 00:04:51,630
How To Read And Trade Market Fractals
The fractal pattern reveals a “V” or “U”

68
00:04:51,630 --> 00:04:53,790
shaped bottom or top.

69
00:04:53,790 --> 00:04:58,570
Such a pattern of price action may indicate
a market reversal – either a previous up

70
00:04:58,570 --> 00:05:03,720
trending market gradually turning over to
the downside, or a previous down trending

71
00:05:03,720 --> 00:05:05,480
market turning to the upside.

72
00:05:05,480 --> 00:05:12,220
At a minimum, a fractal pattern is useful
for identifying at least a temporary level

73
00:05:12,220 --> 00:05:18,760
of price support (with a bullish fractal)
or price resistance (with a bearish fractal).

74
00:05:18,760 --> 00:05:23,470
So you can use fractals to determine the possible
direction of price.

75
00:05:23,470 --> 00:05:28,130
One way in which you could do this, is by
looking for broken fractals.

76
00:05:28,130 --> 00:05:33,570
A fractal is considered broken when it has
been confirmed and then the price breaks through

77
00:05:33,570 --> 00:05:36,350
either the high or the low of the pattern.

78
00:05:36,350 --> 00:05:43,130
If the price breaks an up fractal then the
direction of the market is considered up and

79
00:05:43,130 --> 00:05:49,300
if the price breaks a down fractal then the
market is considered down.

80
00:05:49,300 --> 00:05:50,880
But this is not enough.

81
00:05:50,880 --> 00:05:54,820
On their own, fractals will offer many false
signals.

82
00:05:54,820 --> 00:05:59,880
As a standalone price action tool, fractals
are quite unreliable.

83
00:05:59,880 --> 00:06:03,560
The main problem with fractals is that there
are so many of them.

84
00:06:03,560 --> 00:06:09,240
Therefore, to get the best out of them, you
must filter the signals with some other indicators

85
00:06:09,240 --> 00:06:11,280
or forms of analysis.

86
00:06:11,280 --> 00:06:17,960
You must view a fractal pattern in relation
to other confluence factors, such as support/resistance

87
00:06:17,960 --> 00:06:24,640
levels, supply and demand areas, pivot points,
Fibonacci levels or round numbers, in order

88
00:06:24,640 --> 00:06:27,660
to evaluate the strength of the fractal.

89
00:06:27,660 --> 00:06:33,670
For example, if the high point of a bearish
fractal coincides with a supply area that

90
00:06:33,670 --> 00:06:39,660
also identifies that price point as a potential
resistance level, then the fractal pattern

91
00:06:39,660 --> 00:06:45,950
is more reliable – and more likely to be
an accurate indicator of a market reversal.

92
00:06:45,950 --> 00:06:52,740
Trend Continuation & Breakouts
Fractals can help assessing the potential

93
00:06:52,740 --> 00:06:54,460
direction of a price move.

94
00:06:54,460 --> 00:07:00,330
For example, if a down fractal has recently
printed on the price chart and the overall

95
00:07:00,330 --> 00:07:05,050
trend is higher, then we can expect price
to continue higher.

96
00:07:05,050 --> 00:07:11,170
Along the same lines, if an up fractal has
recently been breached by a new price leg

97
00:07:11,170 --> 00:07:17,360
that is moving higher, that upside breakout
can indicate that price momentum may continue

98
00:07:17,360 --> 00:07:18,360
higher.

99
00:07:18,360 --> 00:07:24,470
So, if the market is in a strong uptrend,
there will be more fractals that are broken

100
00:07:24,470 --> 00:07:27,090
to the upside than the downside.

101
00:07:27,090 --> 00:07:32,510
That being said, the inability to break through
the previous fractal can give you a hint that

102
00:07:32,510 --> 00:07:38,130
the market is getting ready to consolidate,
or perhaps even change trends.

103
00:07:38,130 --> 00:07:43,490
The question then is whether or not the market
is going to turn around and break through

104
00:07:43,490 --> 00:07:48,380
the opposite direction fractal, because at
that point, the previous trend very well could

105
00:07:48,380 --> 00:07:50,820
be rolling over and changing.

106
00:07:50,820 --> 00:07:56,370
Fractals + Moving Average or AVWAP

107
00:07:56,370 --> 00:08:00,930
Another way to use Fractals is with a moving
average or with Anchored VWAP.

108
00:08:00,930 --> 00:08:05,120
I’ve talked about the power of this tool
in this video.

109
00:08:05,120 --> 00:08:10,700
Adding a dynamic level of support and resistance
allows you to stay on the right side of the

110
00:08:10,700 --> 00:08:11,700
trend.

111
00:08:11,700 --> 00:08:17,030
For example, if you get a fractal that forms
in the other direction of the trend, you simply

112
00:08:17,030 --> 00:08:23,050
ignore it, at least until the moving average
or VWAP tell you it’s time to go in that

113
00:08:23,050 --> 00:08:25,270
direction as well.

114
00:08:25,270 --> 00:08:30,300
If you have a 50 period exponential moving
average that is moving to the upside, then

115
00:08:30,300 --> 00:08:36,209
you are looking for up fractals being broken
as you not only have the fractal indicator

116
00:08:36,209 --> 00:08:41,649
pointing in that direction, but you have the
longer-term traders supporting the move as

117
00:08:41,649 --> 00:08:42,649
well.

118
00:08:42,649 --> 00:08:49,290
Or, if a down fractal appears and is located
near the moving average, then you can treat

119
00:08:49,290 --> 00:08:55,140
the previous move as a pullback, with price
founding support in an uptrend, near a moving

120
00:08:55,140 --> 00:08:56,140
average.

121
00:08:56,140 --> 00:09:02,389
3 confluence factors that signal that the
price is more likely to continue higher.

122
00:09:02,389 --> 00:09:07,660
Fractals & Trade management process

123
00:09:07,660 --> 00:09:11,300
Fractals can also be used during the trade
management process.

124
00:09:11,300 --> 00:09:17,620
We know that an up fractal can serve as resistance
during a rising market, and that a down fractal

125
00:09:17,620 --> 00:09:20,800
can serve as support during a declining market.

126
00:09:20,800 --> 00:09:27,140
As such, you can use these important levels
for the placement of stop loss and take profit

127
00:09:27,140 --> 00:09:28,300
orders.

128
00:09:28,300 --> 00:09:33,980
When multiple fractals appear around the same
area, let’s say a resistance area, you can

129
00:09:33,980 --> 00:09:39,740
set your stop loss level when entering a short
position above the highest fractal.

130
00:09:39,740 --> 00:09:45,350
Make sure you don’t place it right above
or below a fractal, leave a bigger margin,

131
00:09:45,350 --> 00:09:49,580
in case there’s some sort of liquidity hunt.

132
00:09:49,580 --> 00:09:54,379
Taking profits could also involve the use
of fractals.

133
00:09:54,379 --> 00:09:59,240
For example, if going long on a fractal, you
could exit the position once a price hits

134
00:09:59,240 --> 00:10:00,370
a bearish fractal.

135
00:10:00,370 --> 00:10:06,009
I heard some traders close their positions
when an opposite fractal appears, but this

136
00:10:06,009 --> 00:10:12,129
is a bad money management approach, because
the fractal signal will lag by a couple of

137
00:10:12,129 --> 00:10:13,129
bars.

138
00:10:13,129 --> 00:10:18,220
At least two closed bars are needed for a
fractal to be completed, meaning that when

139
00:10:18,220 --> 00:10:23,570
it provides a signal, the price may be at
another level compared to the signal.

140
00:10:23,570 --> 00:10:27,760
So don’t rely on this approach to take profits.

141
00:10:27,760 --> 00:10:33,790
Fractals are excellent for visualizing major
highs and lows and act as a support and resistance

142
00:10:33,790 --> 00:10:34,790
level.

143
00:10:34,790 --> 00:10:40,660
A better approach to take profits is a few
points above or below previous fractals.

144
00:10:40,660 --> 00:10:44,420
Multiple time frames approach

145
00:10:44,420 --> 00:10:50,140
It is best to plot fractals in multiple time
frames.

146
00:10:50,140 --> 00:10:55,350
For example, trade short-term fractals in
the direction of the long-term ones.

147
00:10:55,350 --> 00:11:03,149
And focus on long signals during larger uptrends,
and on short signals during larger downtrends.

148
00:11:03,149 --> 00:11:08,149
In day trading setups for example, you could
base your trades on support and resistance

149
00:11:08,149 --> 00:11:13,269
areas offered by fractals on 4hour and daily
chart.

150
00:11:13,269 --> 00:11:18,720
You can check the 30 minutes or the hourly
time frame to look for entries, but you’ll

151
00:11:18,720 --> 00:11:25,589
use fractal periods on the higher timeframes
to spot support and resistance areas.

152
00:11:25,589 --> 00:11:31,589
In this example, you look for reactions at
this resistance level, given by the fractals

153
00:11:31,589 --> 00:11:37,430
on H4 and Daily time frame and trade on 30M
timeframe.

154
00:11:37,430 --> 00:11:43,199
Trading in lower timeframe lets you to read
price action while watching important support

155
00:11:43,199 --> 00:11:46,189
/ resistance levels on higher timeframe.

156
00:11:46,189 --> 00:11:52,649
If price breaks this major resistance here,
it can be a potential breakout setup.

157
00:11:52,649 --> 00:11:57,790
If it rejects the resistance, it can be a
decent reversal setup.

158
00:11:57,790 --> 00:12:03,800
This price action approach might not be suited
for beginner traders, but if you are an experienced

159
00:12:03,800 --> 00:12:10,410
trader, fractals could be of great help, perfect
for finding areas of value on your chart.

160
00:12:10,410 --> 00:12:13,470
Look for areas where multiple fractals form.

161
00:12:13,470 --> 00:12:15,910
And mark those areas.

162
00:12:15,910 --> 00:12:22,139
If multiple fractals form around a certain
level, and price is unable to go through,

163
00:12:22,139 --> 00:12:25,490
that zone is an important one.

164
00:12:25,490 --> 00:12:29,329
Fractals limitations

165
00:12:29,329 --> 00:12:33,129
Now let’s be clear, Fractals do not predict
the price.

166
00:12:33,129 --> 00:12:35,499
They offer lagging signals.

167
00:12:35,499 --> 00:12:41,200
The arrows for the pattern are typically drawn
over the high or low point, which is the middle

168
00:12:41,200 --> 00:12:44,579
of the fractal, not where the fractal completes.

169
00:12:44,579 --> 00:12:47,730
Therefore, the arrows can be visually deceiving.

170
00:12:47,730 --> 00:12:54,360
So be careful, since the pattern is actually
completing two bars to the right of the arrow,

171
00:12:54,360 --> 00:13:00,110
the first available entry point after seeing
an arrow is the opening price of the third

172
00:13:00,110 --> 00:13:02,269
bar to the right of the arrow.

173
00:13:02,269 --> 00:13:07,660
I wouldn’t base my entries on the appearance
of a single fractal.

174
00:13:07,660 --> 00:13:13,399
Fractals has practical meaning only as part
of a comprehensive strategy, and only for

175
00:13:13,399 --> 00:13:17,240
periods of more than one hour.

176
00:13:17,240 --> 00:13:22,649
Another disadvantage of trading fractals is
the fact they occur quite frequently in the

177
00:13:22,649 --> 00:13:29,580
ordinary course of price action movement – therefore,
the pattern is prone to giving many false

178
00:13:29,580 --> 00:13:30,580
signals.

179
00:13:30,580 --> 00:13:36,670
That’s why few traders rely only on the
fractal indicator for trading signals, instead

180
00:13:36,670 --> 00:13:41,559
they are using it in conjunction with other
technical indicators.

181
00:13:41,559 --> 00:13:48,009
Remember: the longer the time period of the
chart, the more reliable the pattern.

182
00:13:48,009 --> 00:13:53,759
So look for fractals on the hourly, H4 and
daily time frames.

